COPY public.ai_global_memory (id, instruction, source, is_active, created_at) FROM stdin;
3	Ignore the keyword 'ATM' or "ATMA" in a transaction description. This DOES NOT mean it is an ATM related transaction. ATMA stands for Association of Taxation and Management Accountants, and means something else.	manual_rulebook	t	2026-02-15 04:09:47.851546
4	Look at the first few keywords, and do a google search. That is probably a better indicator of what the transaction actually is. This applies only the HSBC transaction csv files.	manual_rulebook	t	2026-02-15 04:10:26.616678
5	If a transaction is a large positive amount (> $1000) and contains 'Payroll', 'Salary', or your employer's name, classify as 'Income > Salary'.	manual_rulebook	t	2026-02-15 04:13:27.983975
6	Distinguish 'Groceries' from 'Eating Out'. Supermarkets (Coles, Woolworths, Aldi) are 'Groceries'. Fast food, cafes, and restaurants (McDonalds, Uber Eats, DoorDash) are 'Eating Out'.	manual_rulebook	t	2026-02-15 04:13:46.452655
7	If a transaction repeats exactly every month with the same amount, categorize as 'Bills' or 'Subscriptions' rather than general spending, even if the merchant is generic (e.g. Apple, Google).	manual_rulebook	t	2026-02-15 04:14:25.529767
8	Insurance providers: NRMA, AAMI, Allianz, Bupa, RAC, Medibank, HCF:\n- Health related -> 'Health & Fitness > Health Insurance'.\n- Car related -> 'Transportation > Car Insurance'.	manual_rulebook	t	2026-02-15 04:21:15.041081
9	Transactions with STEAM involved should generally be classed as "Fun"	review_coaching	t	2026-02-15 05:13:35.77684
\.


